This article is a transcript of a background briefing given by a Senior Administration Official on Air Force Two en route to Kabul, Afghanistan. The briefing provides an overview of Vice President Biden's visit to Afghanistan, including his meetings with General Petraeus, Ambassador Eikenberry, and President Karzai. The official discusses the importance of assessing the progress made towards the transition of Afghan lead and responsibility, as well as the ongoing commitment to establish a long-term bilateral relationship between the United States and Afghanistan. The official also addresses questions about the goal of having all combat forces withdrawn by 2014, the reduction of U.S. forces this year, and the issue of corruption in Afghanistan.